Package com.vaadin.polymer.paper

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PaperBadgeElement
    <paper-badge> is a circular text badge that is displayed on the top right
    corner of an element, representing a status or a notification.
    PaperButtonBehavior  
    PaperButtonElement
    Material design: Buttons
    PaperCardElement
    Material design: Cards
    PaperCheckboxElement
    Material design: Checkbox
    PaperCheckedElementBehavior
    Use Polymer.PaperCheckedElementBehavior to implement a custom element
    that has a checked property similar to Polymer.IronCheckedElementBehavior
    and is compatible with having a ripple effect.
    PaperDialogBehavior
    Use Polymer.PaperDialogBehavior and paper-dialog-shared-styles.html to implement a Material Design
    dialog.
    PaperDialogElement
    Material design: Dialogs
    PaperDialogScrollableElement
    Material design: Dialogs
    PaperDrawerPanelElement
    Material design: Navigation drawer
    PaperDropdownMenuElement
    Material design: Dropdown menus
    PaperDropdownMenuLightElement
    Material design: Dropdown menus
    PaperFabElement
    Material design: Floating Action Button
    PaperHeaderPanelElement
    paper-header-panel contains a header section and a content panel section.
    PaperIconButtonElement
    Material design: Icon toggles
    PaperIconButtonLightElement  
    PaperIconItemElement
    <paper-icon-item> is a convenience element to make an item with icon.
    PaperInkyFocusBehavior
    Polymer.PaperInkyFocusBehavior implements a ripple when the element has keyboard focus.
    PaperInputAddonBehavior
    Use Polymer.PaperInputAddonBehavior to implement an add-on for <paper-input-container>.
    PaperInputBehavior
    Use Polymer.PaperInputBehavior to implement inputs with <paper-input-container>.
    PaperInputCharCounterElement
    <paper-input-char-counter> is a character counter for use with <paper-input-container>.
    PaperInputContainerElement
    <paper-input-container> is a container for a <label>, an <input is="iron-input"> or
    <textarea> and optional add-on elements such as an error message or character
    counter, used to implement Material Design text fields.
    PaperInputElement
    Material design: Text fields
    PaperInputErrorElement
    <paper-input-error> is an error message for use with <paper-input-container>.
    PaperItemBehavior  
    PaperItemBodyElement
    Use <paper-item-body> in a <paper-item> or <paper-icon-item> to make two- or
    three- line items.
    PaperItemElement
    Material design: Lists
    PaperListboxElement
    Material design: Menus
    PaperMaterialElement
    Material design: Cards
    PaperMenuButtonElement
    Material design: Dropdown buttons
    PaperMenuElement
    Material design: Menus
    PaperMenuGrowHeightAnimationElement  
    PaperMenuGrowWidthAnimationElement  
    PaperMenuShrinkHeightAnimationElement  
    PaperMenuShrinkWidthAnimationElement  
    PaperProgressElement
    Material design: Progress & activity
    PaperRadioButtonElement
    Material design: Radio button
    PaperRadioGroupElement
    Material design: Radio button
    PaperRippleBehavior
    Polymer.PaperRippleBehavior dynamically implements a ripple
    when the element has focus via pointer or keyboard.
    PaperRippleElement
    Material design: Surface reaction
    PaperScrollHeaderPanelElement
    Material design: Scrolling techniques
    PaperSliderElement
    Material design: Sliders
    PaperSpinnerBehavior  
    PaperSpinnerElement
    Material design: Progress & activity
    PaperSpinnerLiteElement
    Material design: Progress & activity
    PaperStylesElement
    The <paper-styles> component provides simple ways to use Material Design CSS styles
    in your application.
    PaperSubmenuElement
    <paper-submenu> is a nested menu inside of a parent <paper-menu>.
    PaperTabElement
    paper-tab is styled to look like a tab.
    PaperTabsElement
    Material design: Tabs
    PaperTextareaElement
    <paper-textarea> is a multi-line text field with Material Design styling.
    PaperToastElement
    Material design: Snackbards & toasts
    PaperToggleButtonElement
    Material design: Switch
    PaperToolbarElement
    Material design: Toolbars
    PaperTooltipElement
    Material design: Tooltips
